{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop GCSE exams",
        "additional_details": "We think this could lead to:\r\n \r\n~Reduced stress \u2013 exams can put extreme pressure on students\u2019 mental health.\r\n~Fairer grading \u2013 continuous assessment may show true ability, not just exams.\r\n~Real learning \u2013 focus on understanding, not memorization.\r\n~Support for creativity \u2013 lets students show skills beyond written tests.\r\n",
        "background": "We call on the Government to scrap GCSE exams and replace them with fairer continuous assessments, coursework, and smaller tests. We think this would reduce stress, improve mental health, and better prepare students for future education.",
